    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> Also with the new connector of v2, this wouldn't require a change, just a new rendering.\r\n\r\n@bobylito Sorry to resurrect this thread, but I dug into this and have some follow-up questions.\r\n\r\nSo, I ended up getting this working simply by copying https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/feat/instantsearch.js/v2/src/widgets/refinement-list/refinement-list.js into my project, making all the import references non-relative, and tweaking what I needed to.\r\n\r\nWorks, but still seems like overkill for this particular tweak (since I wanted to keep 99% of the default refinementList rendering). Perhaps there should be an easier way to add data to the templates? Assuming I could get at the facet value counts, it seems like adding `header` to `RefinementListTransforms` could be a way to achieve this: https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/widgets/refinementList.html#struct-RefinementListTransforms\r\n\r\nLet me know what you think.",
    "created_at": "2017-05-30T12:14:15Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/2157#issuecomment-304859477",
    "id": 304859477,
    "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2157",
    "node_id": "MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMwNDg1OTQ3Nw==",
