    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@bobylito Certainly, here's the implementation: https://gist.github.com/timkelty/7186587110e649b210d3f948e5420b5f\r\n\r\n> I understand that ultimately it feels a lot of work and copying the inner mechanics of InstantSearch.js is not something that we want to promote either.\r\n\r\nTo be fair, it was actually quite easy - the unfortunate part is now my refinementList widget has to be maintained separately. It does, of course, still use the connector, so the entire refinementList logic didn't need to be copied.\r\n",
